# Write tests ({{ ip }}, phase 3)

## Precondition

Phase 2 done: `make -C sim run TEST={{ ip }}_smoke_test` passes with
`UVM_ERROR : 0` against the real RTL. See `implement-agents.prompt.md`.

## Goal

Extend `seq_lib/` and `tests/` toward the verification plan, and register
every new test in the regression vsif.

## Relevant files

* `seq_lib/{{ ip }}_base_vseq.sv` — base class for every new virtual sequence
  (p_sequencer gives handles to all agent sequencers; ALWAYS null-check them)
* `seq_lib/{{ ip }}_seq_lib_pkg.sv` — add include lines for new sequences
{% for a in agents %}
* `agents/{{ a.name }}_agent/{{ ip }}_{{ a.name }}_base_seq.sv` — extend for directed '{{ a.name }}' stimulus
{% endfor %}
* `tests/{{ ip }}_base_test.sv` — base class for every new test; override
  `configure_env()` to tweak `{{ ip }}_env_cfg` per test
* `tests/{{ ip }}_test_pkg.sv` — add include lines for new tests
* `sim/{{ vsif_name }}` — REGISTER each new test (group/test/count/seed
  random, run_script calling `make run` — copy the smoke pattern)
* `env/{{ ip }}_scoreboard.sv` — fill the `TODO(scoreboard)` compare logic as
  checks become meaningful

## Rules

* Tests configure behavior exclusively through `{{ ip }}_env_cfg` (fields,
  `params`, factory overrides) — never by editing env/agent code per test.
* Parameter-dependent stimulus/checks read the configuration from
  `{{ ip }}_env_cfg` typed mirrors (`prm_*`) or `params[...]` — a test must
  behave correctly under every `cfg/*.yaml`.
* Keep tests seed-stable: no time-dependent randomness outside UVM seeding.

## Commands

```bash
make -C sim run TEST=<new_test>                          # per test while developing
make -C sim run TEST=<new_test> CFG=cfg/<config>.yaml    # against other configs
make -C sim regress                                      # full vsif under vManager
```

## Done when

Every new test passes locally under at least the default configuration, is
included in `tests/{{ ip }}_test_pkg.sv`, and has a `test` entry in
`sim/{{ vsif_name }}`. Then continue with `triage-regression.prompt.md`.
